## Key Commands

```bash
# Tier 2 pipeline (safe, uses Gemini/OpenAI)
applypilot run discover                        # Find new jobs
applypilot run enrich                          # Fetch full descriptions
applypilot run score --limit 100               # AI scoring
applypilot run tailor --limit 50               # Tailor resumes (score >= 7)
applypilot run cover                           # Generate cover letters
applypilot run pdf                             # Generate PDFs
applypilot run score tailor cover --stream     # Multiple stages concurrently
applypilot status                              # Pipeline funnel stats
applypilot dashboard                           # Generate and open HTML dashboard

# Tier 3 apply (uses Claude Code credits)
applypilot apply                               # Auto-apply (5 workers, continuous)
applypilot apply --url URL --dry-run           # Test a single job
applypilot apply --workers 3 --min-score 9     # Tune parallelism and score floor
applypilot apply --fresh-sessions              # Refresh Chrome cookies first
applypilot apply --sessions                    # List saved ATS sessions
applypilot apply --clear-session workday       # Clear an ATS session
applypilot apply --reset-failed                # Retry all failed jobs
applypilot apply --reset-category CATEGORY     # Retry jobs in a category
applypilot apply --mark-applied URL            # Manually mark applied
applypilot apply --mark-failed URL --fail-reason "reason"
applypilot human-review                        # HITL server for parked jobs

# Post-apply tracking
applypilot track                               # Scan Gmail for responses

# Q&A knowledge base
applypilot qa list
applypilot qa stats
applypilot qa export --output qa.yaml
applypilot qa import qa.yaml

# Credentials
applypilot creds list
applypilot creds show DOMAIN
applypilot creds add DOMAIN
applypilot creds import-logs
```

---

## Orchestration Strategy

1. **Throughput** — use `--stream` for concurrent stages
2. **Quality** — highest scores get tailored first
3. **Error handling** — if > 30% failure rate, stop and fix before continuing
4. **Bottleneck focus** — priority is building the apply-ready queue

Error patterns:
- Gemini 429: automatic fallback, no intervention needed
- Tailor validation failures > 30%: investigate validator settings
- Apply credit exhaustion: alert user, cannot auto-fix

